history.content:
This is quite normal for some classes. A 999 section is simply a filler section for enrollment. You'll "pick" an actual discussion time once classes begin.

The purpose of 999 sections is to negate the idea that someone can enroll in lecture and be wait listed for discussion and vice versa.

The benefit of 999 sections is that (most of the time, not always) classes that have such sections typically encourage students to try out multiple discussion sections in the first few weeks to see if they prefer any particular time or TA.

When I try to enroll in CS 188, CS170, and Data 100, I don't get the discussion sections. I get enrolled in the discussion section COMPSCI C100-999
(28044), 	
COMPSCI 170-999
(28054), and
COMPSCI 188-999
(28057), with no GSI/TA or date and time. Is this normal??
history.subject: CS 188, 170, and Data 100 Discussion Sections
